line1: There once was a artist named Marcell
line2: Whose studio housed a man in jail.
line3: When he came to see her,
line4: He was shocked by her fur,
line5: And asked her because she was female.

line1: There once was a phony named Dot
line2: Who put all her money in a pot.
line3: When she tried to sell it,
line5: So she gave up and quit on the spot.

line1: There was an Old Person of Ischia,
line2: Whose conduct grew friskier and friskier;
line5: That lively Old Person of Ischia.

line1: There was a cruel girl named Hyun
line2: Who cried for a long time to someone.
line5: And she left to go to a new one.

line1: There was a neat girl named Leone
line2: Who walked a great distance on her own.
line5: She was able to lift a huge stone.

line1: There was an Old Man in a boat,
line5: That unhappy Old Man in a boat.

line1: There was an Old Man with a beard,
line2: Who said, 'It is just as I feared!
line5: Have all built their nests in my beard!'

line1: Why do we have homework after school?
line5: All of this homework after school.

line1: There was a warrior named Corazon
line2: Who fought a great battle on her own.
line3: She came back from the dead,
line4: With a crown on her head,
line5: And the blood on the floor of the throne.

line1: Lou Costello showed wonder and glee
line2: When we saw him each week on TV
line4: He was one of a kind
line5: Such a jolly good fellow was he
